From 7e26841c675902b05dc4a7699ef8148389cc43f8 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: A7 Shim <a7-shim@local>
Date: Tue, 21 Apr 2026 16:33:57 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 5/5] shim: route socket teardown close through so_instance

socket_close() historically calls libc close(2) on fd->live_fd when
packetdrill shuts a connection down at state_free / close_all_fds
time. Under the A7 shim, live_fd is a synthetic fd (SHIM_FD_BASE=1000
and up) backed by dpdk_net_shim's fd table, not a real kernel fd. The
direct libc close() therefore returns -1/EBADF, which packetdrill
treats as fatal via die_perror("close") -> exit(EXIT_FAILURE), turning
a clean script completion into a spurious non-zero exit and the
"close: Bad file descriptor" stderr line.

Fix: when state->so_instance is populated (i.e. the shim is active),
route the teardown close through so_instance->ifc.close the same way
syscall_close already does in run_system_call.c around line 2510.
This lets dpdk_net_shim's shim_close handler free the fd slot (and
dpdk_net_test_close the underlying connection handle, if any) using
the same path that explicit close() syscalls in the script take.

No behaviour change when so_instance is NULL (classic libc path).
---
 gtests/net/packetdrill/socket.c | 16 +++++++++++++++-
 1 file changed, 15 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/gtests/net/packetdrill/socket.c b/gtests/net/packetdrill/socket.c
index c661c5a..de4d427 100644
--- a/gtests/net/packetdrill/socket.c
+++ b/gtests/net/packetdrill/socket.c
@@ -33,11 +33,25 @@ void socket_close(struct state *state, struct fd_state *fd)
 	struct socket *socket = fd_to_socket(fd);
 
 	if (fd->live_fd >= 0 && !socket->fd.is_closed) {
+		int rc;
 		assert(fd->script_fd >= 0);
 		DEBUGP("closing struct state socket "
 		       "live.fd:%d script.fd:%d\n",
 		       fd->live_fd, fd->script_fd);
-		if (close(fd->live_fd))
+		/* A7 shim: route live-fd teardown through the so_instance
+		 * interface when present, so synthetic fds (e.g. the
+		 * dpdk_net_shim fd-table rooted at SHIM_FD_BASE) go through
+		 * the shim's close handler instead of libc's close(2) --
+		 * calling libc close() on a synthetic fd returns EBADF and
+		 * trips die_perror at teardown. Mirrors run_system_call.c
+		 * syscall_close (circa line 2510). */
+		if (state->so_instance)
+			rc = state->so_instance->ifc.close(
+				state->so_instance->ifc.userdata,
+				fd->live_fd);
+		else
+			rc = close(fd->live_fd);
+		if (rc)
 			die_perror("close");
 	}
 	if (socket->protocol == IPPROTO_TCP &&
-- 
